data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync calls will throw at runtime — with no workaround.**

In EF Core 10, the Cosmos DB provider deprecated sync I/O but allowed an opt-in to keep it working. **EF Core 11 removes that opt-in entirely.** `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` against the Cosmos provider now **always throw**.

You must convert to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple through your call chain — every caller of these methods must also become `async`/`await`. There is no opt-in flag or compatibility shim in EF Core 11 to restore the old sync-over-async behavior.
